                <div id="summary">
                  <h1>Minos Online Judge Project</h1>
                  <p>Competitive programming is a mind sport usually held over the internet or a local network, involving participants trying to program according to provided specifications.</p>
                  <p>Competitive programming is recognized and supported by several multinational software and internet companies, such as Google, Facebook, IBM and Intel.</p>
                  <p>The main idea of the project is to provide a web platform to host these Programming Competitions, we called it Minos Online Judge.</p>
                  <p>Our principal client is the Universidad Nacional de Colombia, because this makes competitions to clasify their teams for the National and Regional Competitions hosted by the ICPC every year.</p>
